{
  "stem": "1062.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Next, what we had what is called a [HEBREW], a [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So in the-- in the wintertime, when it was very, very cold, so you didn't have to heat up the whole shul, so you just went into the [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Next to it, we had another building where the shammash used to live.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Over there was the cheder.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I mean, for the-- for the advanced study cheder.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It was also used for Pesach to bake matzahs because it had a big oven in one room.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And they have the people who used to bake the matzahs.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Now, how they baked matzahs over there, this is a story by itself.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And it's something very hard for American mind to understand the-- the-- how-- how the system worked.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "If you don't mind, if I have a minute, I would like to describe this because this is a very interesting story.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[DRINKS] When they had the grain, the wheat, and what you make matzahs, women would get together from house to house.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And they would pour the wheat on the table.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And they would select each kernel.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "All the impurities was taken out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And then they put it in a bag, all the wheat.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Then the men would get together, and they would go to a mill.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "It was a water mill, which was driven by water.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "They would take off the stone.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And they would chop the bottom of the stone in order to take out all the old flour, so you shouldn't cause chametz, what they call chametz.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they would chop the stone.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They'd chip it until they took off all the stone-- all-- all the-- the pieces from the stone and all-- what everything is-- which was connected to it.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then they-- they would mill it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And after it was milled, brought back to the village.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The-- by the way, this mill was in next village, a village called [?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Batarci. ?]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Then everybody in my village had a job.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For an example, I would give water, to put the water into the-- into the flour.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was called a [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Somebody would give the flour in another site.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He would-- he was called a [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In the middle, there was Reb Shmiel.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was a small guy, with a long white beard.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he would knead the dough.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But it had to be done very fast because if you let the dough stay there, so the dough would rise, and it wouldn't be kosher.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So he did it very fast.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Well, Passover time, we used to find a lot of hair from Shmiel's beard inside the-- inside the-- inside with the matzahs, you know, because he was kneading it so fast, he's-- even his-- you know, piece of the beard would fall in.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But that was OK.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was kosher.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "After they took out the dough from Shmiel's, you know, when he was finished kneading it, there was a long table.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And somebody stood there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He was known as a [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "In other words, he would rip off a piece of the dough and gave it to the woman.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He was known as the [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Woman would stay in line in either side of the table.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Maybe there were about 25, 30 woman.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And they would roll out the matzah.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "After the matzah was rolled out, somebody would take it over to another table, where it would go through a wheel-- a wheel full of spokes, so when the matzah heats up, it shouldn't blow up.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So the matzah has-- I think even-- even today's matzah has little spokes in it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "That's the reasoning.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Even today's matzah has it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They would-- they would roll over with a-- a little wheel with spokes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was known as a reddler.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then somebody would take the matzah and put it on a-- what do you call that rolling stone-- the rolling stick?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There is a name for it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "A rolling pin.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A rolling pin, yeah.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Put it on a rolling pin and bring it over to the-- to the oven.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was known as a [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the guy by the oven, he was known as a shiber.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he would take it and throw it into the oven.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He make-- I would say that from the time you take the-- the-- the flour to the time the matzah comes out, maybe-- maybe it was 14, 15 minutes, the whole-- the whole thing.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this was a community undertaking.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I want you to know that this used to take weeks, weeks to go with the wheat.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It-- but it was a project.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was a big project.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
